I know it's an early prototype, but feels very good and just like an old descent 1/2, exactly as promised!
From now it is very important to stay on track in a development process and do not mess with the core gameplay.

Some issues with the game (if threat it as an actual game, not a prototype :)):
1. X and Y sensitivity (playing with mouse) are NOT equal - why?
2. Didn't found a way to reduce sensitivity in options, with every click it goes up;
3. Enemies are too healthy and even with missiles can't be oneshoted. It's not about difficulty, but about feedback and fun. It is always feels better make them weaker, but put more of them;
4. From a distance it is hard to tell when enemy finally dies. The death explosion not differs much from damage effects and missile impacts;
5. Bad level design, especially in caves. All the passages looks the same: no markers or distinctive props to make places memorable;

I will press NO - but just to make developers read this ;)
In fact I highly recommend this game. Can't wait to put my hands on a final version!
